<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-27T11:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-27T11:45:00-05:00" n="823" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d823">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/645: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jefferson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-27T11:00:00-05:45"><hi rend="italic">May 27,
                                            1919, 11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received May 28, 1.20 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Information received yesterday is to the effect that the Acosta force
                                of 300 men attacked 800 of Tinoco forces at El Jobo near Liberia. It
                                seems that the battle lasted five hours. Losses were sustained on
                                both sides. The Acosta force retired to their base of operations on
                                account of shortage in ammunition. It is reported that Tinoco has in
                                the vicinity of Guanacaste a force of approximately 2,000 men well
                                equipped and fortified.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Jefferson</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>